metadata.name: Refractions #5
metadata.description:
Refractions is a study of frequencies, harmonies and abstract representations of natural phenomena. 

It is an experiment of blending three colors to create integrated textural compositions.


Probabilities;

- 14 compositions with variations.

- 2 background color.

- 19 different base color palette (2 monochrome).

- 2 distinct textures with variations.

-  2 different alpha types; tangential & sinusoidal.

- Different edges.

- Several starting positions and styles (wavy or straight).


Made with p5.js

Ilgın İçözü, April 2022
@distcollective

metadata.name: Pandora #163
metadata.description:
Pandora received many gifts from the Gods: beauty, flattery, kindness, skill, grace, intelligence, but also the art of deception and seduction. They gave her the name Pandora (Πανδώρα), “endowed with all the gifts” in Greek.

The Pandora generative series has the same qualities as the mythological figure. Able to adopt many different shapes, a wide variety of colors and styles, all created from simple rules.

Only one thing though, do not open the box.

[S] key to save a PNG image
Press once for a resolution of 2000x2000, a second time for a resolution of 4000x4000, then 6000x6000 and finally 8000x8000

Made with p5.js

Artist: Estienne
April 2022
License: NFT 2.0

metadata.name: Balanced #246
metadata.description:
What does balance look like when viewed through the lens of pure mathematics? This is the question Balanced attempts to answer.

Each output is composed of a unique collection of blocks mathematically stacked to be in perfect balance.

This is my Genesis project. Enjoy!

Interactions:
1 - Reverse your stack vertically and re-balance.
2 - Toggle between square and portrait frame.
3 - Show center of mass. 
4 - Toggle the border.
5 - Toggle the background (color/transparent)
6 - Export image (2048x2048)
7 - Export image (4096x4096)
8 - Export image (8192x8192)

How it was made: https://www.jeffweber.art/balanced

metadata.name: Bedlam #106
metadata.description:
Originally a study of paint brushes and texture, this project morphed. I started to find a medley of painting with the texture of handmade rugs, leveraging this medium to not just recreate the everyday, but let my imagination run. 

Enjoy each abstract piece that "Bedlam" has to offer, with 25 palettes, 5 brush styles, and an endless combination of stroke lengths and layering effects, there is much to be discovered.

It can take up to a minute for the Painting to finish, depending on your hardware.

Press 's' in Live View to save a png.

On the display, we have preloaded the "Beginner Ideocartography" cartridge. This is a standard introduction to ideocartography, and is widely considered to be mostly safe to perceive.
Your task is to investigate, within a limited range of colors and textures, for the presence of active entities. As you use the arrow keys to explore your layer of <REDACTED>, please record short descriptions of the images you see, and please note any feelings you experience. Most of these entities should be rendered inert via compression into two dimensions (plus time). metadata.name: sun peel stare #107
metadata.description:
have you seen the sky today? (how often do you look?)

will it find you fractured or aligned? (or will it not see you at all?)

what don’t we see when the light is in our eyes? (do we even want to?)

[ in “live view” you can press: ]
[ P : process more/pause ]
[ S or 1 : save 3000x3000 png ]
[ 2 :  save 6000x6000 png ]
[ 3 :  save 12000x12000 png ]

(after initial render, you can save at any point of processing.)
